page.title: 01Lockton High Moor
page.content: Predominantly high, open, heather dominated moorland bisected by the main A169 road. The south east has 1km of conifer plantation and there are some woodlands and plantation in th west in a steep soiled valley along which runs the Nor York shire moors railway. Most of the area to east of the road is Ministry of Defence property and has the Fybngdales early warning staion. The only residents of the block are the forces personnel who work there. Sheep graze the area ad there are some cattle on rough grazing in the south. Because of access problems the area is not heavily visited by tourists or walkers although the high moors and the valley to te east make spectacular scenery for those driving through or viewing from further south.
